title: For Sale:  CZ-82 czech 9x18 makarov military pistol
postcontent:
This is a great pistol that is in great used condition, I prefer it over 9mm. Unfortunately I have flood damage and must liquidate some assets.

Meet in Boulder on Saturdays, will include FFL Fee $350

Comes with:

-Original Holster, lanyard w/clip
-New Bulldog holster, w/ belt and molle attachment, and spare magazine holster
-2x 12round double stack Magazines
-100 rounds Boxed 9mm Makarov Silver bear.
-Classified as Curio & Relic

Description:

Manufactured by the Czechoslovak firm Česká zbrojovka the vz. 82 replaced the 7.62x25mm Tokarev vz. 52 pistol in Czechoslovak military service in 1983. It is a compact, double-action, semi-automatic pistol with a conventional blowback action. This type of action allows the barrel to remain solidly fixed to the frame, resulting in improved accuracy over pistols with pivoting barrels (like the U.S. M1911 series). The low bore axis of the vz. 82 provides for less muzzle rise and quicker follow-up shots. For added convenience, both the frame-mounted thumb safety and the magazine release are ambidextrous. The vz. 82 was the first service pistol to feature both these features. The bore is chrome plated, which gives it three advantages: longer barrel life, resistance to rust from the use of corrosive ammunition, and ease of cleaning. Another feature of this pistol is the use of polygonal rifling in the barrel bore. This replaces the traditional lands and grooves rifling design with a rounded, smooth polygonal pattern which has a more "hills and valleys" appearance.

The United States Navy Mark 12 Mod 0/1 Special Purpose Rifle (SPR) is a rifle in service with United States Special Operations Forces in Operation Enduring Freedom and previously in Operation Iraqi Freedom. title: For Sale/Trade:  Kimber Ultra Raptor Stainless II, Sig P220R, Upgraded Glock 27 Gen.4
postcontent: I have 3 guns I'm willing to trade. The 1st is a Kimber Ultra Raptor in stainless steel. It has 3 Kimber 8 round stainless mags, and a leather iwb custom holster. It has around 200 rounds through it, and is in mint condition. The 2nd gun is a Sig Sauer P220R with Night Sights, Hogue Grips, and 3 8 round factory mags. Not sure of the round count because I'm not the original owner, but it has been well taken maintained, and is in great shape. The 3rd gun is the most expensive. It is a Glock 27 Gen.4 with about $1,350.00 in parts and gunsmith labor. If you want a stock Glock this isn't for you, and if you don't think guns should be modified this isn't for you, but I didn't just order parts, and throw them on the gun. It is by far more accurate, better feel, less recoil, and 1000x better trigger than a factory Glock. It is just as reliable as a factory Glock, and is an amazing carry gun. It has a Zev Tech black on black Fulcrum trigger pad, trigger bar, and ejector housing, which is set up with a 3.0 lb. self defense trigger pull, but can be adjusted to 2 lbs. up too 6 lbs.I also have the pre travel and over travel set up for self defense so it isn't a hair trigger, but it can be adjusted as well to have no pre travel or over travel, but i would not use it for self defense or a carry gun if you choose to set it up with no travel in the trigger. that is competition settings. It also reduces the travel reset of the trigger by 50%. This trigger is super crisp, and breaks better than my Kimber 1911 trigger. By far the bet trigger you can put on a glock. It has a 3.5 Ghost Evo trigger connecter, or I can install the Zev Tech V4 race connector, but will come with both. It has a lightning Strike titanium polished safety plunger with a reduced power plunger spring, or I can install the Zev Tech polished safety plunger, but again it will come with both. I also have 3 standard power springs for the safety plungers. It has a Zev Tech polished, skeletonized, stainless striker pin, with a 6 lb. firing pin spring, but I also have a 4 lb. and 5 lb. firing pin spring for it. ( I highly recommend the 6 lb. spring for a self defense set up.) it has a tungsten recoil assembly with a 16lb. double spring captured, that is 5x heavier than the stock polymer recoil spring, and 2x heavier than a stainless steel recoil assembly, which helps tremendously by reducing lock time by 58% and reducing muzzle flip and felt recoil dramatically. It has a 6lb. Trigger spring, and I have a 5 lb. trigger spring for it as well. It has a KKM Precision stainless match grade barrel that was match fitted by a Master Glock Armorer. It still has enough play to digest all ammo, but locks up tighter for better accuracy. It has a Vickers Tactical Tangodown Mag release, and slide catch, and +1 Pearce Grip Extensions on all 3 mags to make them 10 round mags. It also has marine spring cups for better reliability. It makes it easier to shoot in harsh conditions, and an I-Tac owb button release holster. I have all the factory parts I replaced I.e. barrel, trigger assembly, guide rod etc. It was worth every penny I spent on it, but I'm ready to build something else. I can sen pics of any of the guns if interested.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Kimber Ultra Raptor II Stainless, Sig P220R, Upgraded Glock 27 Gen.4
postcontent: I have 3 guns I'm willing to trade. The 1st is a Kimber Ultra Raptor in stainless steel. It has 3 Kimber 8 round stainless mags, and a leather iwb custom holster. It has around 200 rounds through it, and is in mint condition. The 2nd gun is a Sig Sauer P220R with Night Sights, Hogue Grips, and 3 8 round factory mags. Not sure of the round count because I'm not the original owner, but it has been well taken maintained, and is in great shape. The 3rd gun is the most expensive. It is a Glock 27 Gen.4 with about $1,350.00 in parts and gunsmith labor. If you want a stock Glock this isn't for you, and if you don't think guns should be modified this isn't for you, but I didn't just order parts, and throw them on the gun. It is by far more accurate, better feel, less recoil, and 1000x better trigger than a factory Glock. It is just as reliable as a factory Glock, and is an amazing carry gun. It has a Zev Tech black on black Fulcrum trigger pad, trigger bar, and ejector housing, which is set up with a 3.0 lb. self defense trigger pull, but can be adjusted to 2 lbs. up too 6 lbs.I also have the pre travel and over travel set up for self defense so it isn't a hair trigger, but it can be adjusted as well to have no pre travel or over travel, but i would not use it for self defense or a carry gun if you choose to set it up with no travel in the trigger. that is competition settings. It also reduces the travel reset of the trigger by 50%. This trigger is super crisp, and breaks better than my Kimber 1911 trigger. By far the bet trigger you can put on a glock. It has a 3.5 Ghost Evo trigger connecter, or I can install the Zev Tech V4 race connector, but will come with both. It has a lightning Strike titanium polished safety plunger with a reduced power plunger spring, or I can install the Zev Tech polished safety plunger, but again it will come with both. I also have 3 standard power springs for the safety plungers. It has a Zev Tech polished, skeletonized, stainless striker pin, with a 6 lb. firing pin spring, but I also have a 4 lb. and 5 lb. firing pin spring for it. ( I highly recommend the 6 lb. spring for a self defense set up.) it has a tungsten recoil assembly with a 16lb. double spring captured, that is 5x heavier than the stock polymer recoil spring, and 2x heavier than a stainless steel recoil assembly, which helps tremendously by reducing lock time by 58% and reducing muzzle flip and felt recoil dramatically. It has a 6lb. Trigger spring, and I have a 5 lb. trigger spring for it as well. It has a KKM Precision stainless match grade barrel that was match fitted by a Master Glock Armorer. It still has enough play to digest all ammo, but locks up tighter for better accuracy. It has a Vickers Tactical Tangodown Mag release, and slide catch, and +1 Pearce Grip Extensions on all 3 mags to make them 10 round mags. It also has marine spring cups for better reliability. It makes it easier to shoot in harsh conditions, and an I-Tac owb button release holster. I have all the factory parts I replaced I.e. barrel, trigger assembly, guide rod etc. It was worth every penny I spent on it, but I'm ready to build something else. I can sen pics of any of the guns if interested.

title: For Trade:  Upgraded Glock 27 Gen.4 with tons of Modifications
postcontent: I have a custom Glock 27 Gen. 4 with a lot of modifications. It has a Zev Tech Fulcrum Trigger, with adjustable pre-travel and over travel, and can be adjusted from a 2 lb. trigger pull up to a 6 lb. trigger pull, and has 50% less trigger reset travel than stock. It's currently set up at 3.0 lbs. and average pre-travel for everyday carry. It has a Zev-Tech stainless steel polished skeletonized striker with a 4lb. Striker spring, and marine cups. It has a KKM Precision match grade barrel that was match fitted by KKM. It has a Tungsten Recoil double spring assembly that's 5x heavier than the factory polymer recoil assembly, and 2x heavier than a stainless recoil assembly. It really does reduce muzzle flip and recoil. It has a Zev Tech ejector housing with adjustable over travel, and a Lightning Strike polished titanium safety plunger with a reduced power safety plunger spring. It has a Ghost Evo 3.5 lb. connector with a 6lb. Trigger spring. Also has +1 Pearce Grip extensions on all 3 mags, and a Vickers Tactical Tango Down mag release, and slide catch. I also installed Trijicon night sights on it, and I have all the factory parts that I replaced to go with it. You can truly tell a huge difference in this gun and shooting a stock Glock. The mods aren't necessary, but are well worth the money if you want a nicer glock. If you are looking for a stock Glock this gun isn't for you. It's for the guy who wants a Glock that is heads and tails better than any other polymer frame pistol out there right now. It shoots amazingly, and has the best trigger of any gun I've shot that wasn't a $2,000.00 or more 1911, and I've shot them all. It's basically all the upgrades and match grade parts you find in a $2,000.00 1911, but in a Glock Platform. I'm just ready to move on, and build something else.

postcontent:
This is a new in the box KSG shotgun

It has the updated internals/cartridge stop

KSG
The KSG ejects downward and is fully ambidextrous. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1” overall length and an 18.5” cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 13 rounds of 12 gauge 3” rounds in total (6 per tube + 1 in the chamber) 15 rounds of 2 3/4" (7 per tube + 1 in the chamber). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 3".

This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.

The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.

The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.
